The paper deals with the Rural Postman Problem, which is a graph theory problem. The paper discusses the complexity of the problem and provides a polynomial-size approximate kernelization scheme. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which suggests the category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The problem involves graphs, which suggests the category cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests the category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses kernelization, which suggests the category cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
